My name is Liam and I am 13. Ever  since I was 7 I've been bullied for being short, and weird, or different. I have complications with type one diabetes and this is why I am so short. So many times I have though of giving up, and just not bothering to go to school, or even get up in the morning, but I managed to pull through. I learned to take it on the chin, and just live and let live. No matter how much people get you down, or make you feel like nothing, just keep pushing yourself, an don't give in. There are infinite numbers between 0 and 1. There's .1 and .12 and .112 and an infinite collection of others. Of course, there is a bigger infinite set of numbers between 0 and 2, or between 0 and a million. Some infinities are bigger than other infinities. A writer we used to like taught us that. There are days, many of them, when I resent the size of my unbounded set. I want more numbers than I'm likely to get, and God, I want more numbers for Augustus Waters than he got. But, Gus, my love, I cannot tell you how thankful I am for our little infinity. I wouldn't trade it for the world. You gave me a forever within the numbered days, and I'm grateful.

"A boy, a blond, kind, sociable, athletic boy who likes writing love poems and boxing, and who knows how to give his all to everything he does, meets a girl. A girl who is gorgeous, smart, elegant, and yet distant from everyone. Despite their differences, as they start talking to each other day after day, it seems that both of them are the same. Two sides of the same coin. The one shares his kindness unconditionally even if it hurts him, and the other is afraid to show any sort of love to anyone. Slowly the years pass by, and in three years time, they become best friends, and both develop their lifes, their minds and their bodies, one way or another. She lives in Romania, he lives in Cyprus but studies in the UK. And in christmas of 2016 he visits her for one week, but after that she decides that they should stop talking.
